<task id="task-3479" class="- topic/topic task/task "><title class="- topic/title ">Create BDD test case with Cucumber Hooks</title><taskbody class="- topic/body task/taskbody "><context class="- topic/section task/context ">To create a BDD test case with Cucumber Hooks, follow these steps:</context><steps class="- topic/ol task/steps "><step class="- topic/li task/step "><cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">Set up Cucumber hooks in <ph conkeyref="name-variables/katalon-studio" class="- topic/ph "/>. See: <xref href="../../Manage_Test_Artifacts/Working_With_BDD_Feature_File/set_up_cucumber_hooks.dita" class="- topic/xref ">Set up Cucumber hooks</xref>.</cmd></step><step class="- topic/li task/step "><cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">Create a new test case.</cmd><info class="- topic/itemgroup task/info ">You can refer to this document: <xref href="../Create_A_New_Test_Case/Create_a_new_test_case.dita" class="- topic/xref ">Create a new test case in <ph conkeyref="name-variables/katalon-studio" class="- topic/ph "/></xref>.</info></step><step class="- topic/li task/step "><cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">In the <uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">Manual</uicontrol> view of the new test case, click on the <uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">Add</uicontrol> dropdown button and select <uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">Cucumber Keywords</uicontrol>.</cmd><stepresult class="- topic/itemgroup task/stepresult "><image width="700" href="images/KS-Add-Cucumber-keyword.png" class="- topic/image "><alt class="- topic/alt ">Add Cucumber Keywords</alt></image></stepresult></step><step class="- topic/li task/step "><cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">Select the <uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">Run Feature File</uicontrol> keyword.</cmd><stepresult class="- topic/itemgroup task/stepresult "><image width="700" href="images/KS-select-run-feature-file-keyword.png" class="- topic/image "><alt class="- topic/alt ">Select Run Feature File keyword</alt></image></stepresult></step><step class="- topic/li task/step "><cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">Right-click on the Feature file and select <uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">Copy ID</uicontrol> to get the relative path.</cmd><stepresult class="- topic/itemgroup task/stepresult "><image width="500" href="images/KS-Copy-ID-feature-file.png" class="- topic/image "/></stepresult></step><step class="- topic/li task/step "><cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">Double-click on the <uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">Input</uicontrol> cell of the <uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">Run Feature File</uicontrol> keyword. In the displayed <uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">Input</uicontrol> dialog, paste the copied relative path from step 3 as the input value.</cmd><stepresult class="- topic/itemgroup task/stepresult "><image width="700" href="images/KS-Feature-file-input-value.png" class="- topic/image "><alt class="- topic/alt ">Input feature file value</alt></image></stepresult></step><step class="- topic/li task/step "><cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">Run the test and verify the message of the Cucumber hooks in the <uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">Console</uicontrol> log:</cmd><stepresult class="- topic/itemgroup task/stepresult "><image width="700" href="images/KS-Cucumber-hooks-message.png" class="- topic/image "><alt class="- topic/alt ">Cucumber hooks message</alt></image></stepresult></step></steps></taskbody></task>